    "body": "To whomever works on this: the problem seems to be that one of the sourcemaps (the one for ERC20Mock) starts like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\n:::-;146:146:23;416:163:7;;;;...\r\n```\r\n\r\nI thought this wasn't supposed to be valid, because empty fields are interpreted with the same value as the one in the previous element, so the first one shouldn't be empty. The code seems to make the same assumption:\r\n\r\n```\r\n          parts[0] !== undefined && parts[0] !== \"\"\r\n            ? +parts[0]\r\n            : mappings[i - 1].location.offset,\r\n```\r\n\r\nsince that can be executed when `i === 0`, which is what it seems to be happening here.\r\n\r\nI guess a simple solution is to add a `i === 0` condition there, but what value is supposed to take?",
